benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/block - Retrieve blocking states for account

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios TC01 and TC02 cover retrieval with and without filters for a valid account.
Empty Response: TC08 (account with no blocking states) and TC09 (non-existent account) verify empty array responses.
Query Parameters: TC02 (blockingStateTypes), TC03 (blockingStateSvcs), TC04 (both filters), TC05-TC07 (audit parameter variations) test parameter handling and audit verbosity.
Authorization: TC14-TC15 cover missing and invalid authentication tokens.

Error Handling: TC10 (invalid accountId format) and TC11/TC12 (invalid parameter values) test client error responses, TC16 (service unavailable) and TC25 (dependent service unavailable) cover server-side dependency failures, TC19 (timeout under load) touches latency/timeout behavior, TC17 (large data) and TC01/TC02 with large or varied data.
Regression/Compatibility: TC21 (combined filters), TC20 (backward compatibility with legacy clients), TC26 (data consistency across integrated systems), TC27 (concurrent access).
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for pagination behavior when the dataset is large or when responses are paginated.
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No scenarios validating handling of burst requests or rate limits.
Caching Behavior: No tests asserting caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or client-side caching behavior.
Explicit 403/Authorization Edge Case: Tests cover 401/invalid token but not 403 forbidden scenarios.
Internal Server Error coverage: No explicit 500 Internal Server Error test (server-side exception) beyond 503/service unavailable.
Granular performance thresholds: Only TC19 mentions timeouts but no defined SLA thresholds or benchmarks across scenarios.
recommendations: Add pagination-focused tests to verify proper handling (first/last page, page size limits, and total counts) for large datasets.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure system stability under rapid successive requests.
Add caching validation tests (ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified) and cache-invalidating scenarios.
Include a test for 403 Forbidden to cover authorization nuance in addition to 401/invalid token scenarios.
Add a test simulating 500 Internal Server Error to ensure proper error handling and messaging when a server-side failure occurs.
Enhance performance testing with explicit SLA targets (max response time under load, percentile-based latency) across representative scenarios.
